If the crawler has given up on a seed http://bla.bla in the crawl.log, 
you should see something similar to this:

2007-04-17T21:15:36.734Z    -1          - dns:bla.bla P http://bla.bla/ 
text/dns #003 20070417211536671+47 - - 3t
2007-04-17T21:15:38.734Z    -6          - http://bla.bla/ - - no-type 
#028 - - - 2t

Also, in the progess-statistics.log there should be a line with
&quot;CRAWL ENDED - Finished&quot; entry.

If both are present and the job is still running then something is 
wrong. Try creating a thread dump. That would give you a better idea on 
the state of the threads.

